# Apps & Tools You Need

1. Visual Studio Code
2. Python

# Python Libraries Required

Install these in VS Code terminal:

pip install pandas numpy nltk scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn ,
pip install wordcloud

# Dataset Needed

Use the Kaggle Resume Dataset.

Search:
Resume Dataset

# Create Virtual Environment

Run:

python -m venv venv

Activate it:
Windows
venv\Scripts\activate
If activated correctly, you will see:
(venv)

# Create Main Files

Create these files in VS Code:

app.py ,
preprocess.py ,
train_model.py ,
requirements.txt

# In the VS Code terminal, run this command:

pip install pandas

If you also need all required libraries together, run:

pip install pandas numpy nltk scikit-learn matplotlib seaborn wordcloud

command -   python app.py

# In your VS Code terminal, install NLTK using:

pip install nltk

# Download Required NLTK Resources

Create a file named:
download_nltk.py
Paste this:
import nltk
nltk.download('punkt')
nltk.download('stopwords')

Run:

python download_nltk.py
You will see packages downloading successfully.

# These Resources Are Needed For

punkt → tokenization (splitting sentences/words)
stopwords → removing common words like:
the
is
and
are

